snippet.textDisplay:
COMPLETE RECIPE

cheetos sauce
1 cup honey
1 cup cheetos

spice mix
1/4 cup cheetos powder
1 tsp cayenne (optional)
2 tbsp paprika
1 tbsp mustard powder
1 tbsp onion powder
1 tbsp garlic powder
1 tbsp black pepper

marinated chicken
4 chicken thighs (skin on, bone in)
6 tbsp spice mix

oil mix
1/2 cup canola oil
2 tbsp spice mix
2 tsp brown sugar

dry ingredients
1 1/2 cup flour
3/4 cup cheetos powder
2 tbsp sugar
1 1/2 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp baking soda
1/2 tsp salt

wet ingredients
1/2 cup sour cream
1 1/2 cup buttermilk
4 eggs separated
4 tbsp melted butter (about 60g)

deep frying batter
2 cups buttermilk
2 tbsp hot sauce

Method:
1- Add the cheetos sauce ingredients together into a pot (make sure the cheetos are submerged in the honey) and let it simmer for a few minutes. Then let it sit aside for 15 - 20 minutes.
2- Grind some cheetos into a fine powder.
Create the spice mix by lightly mixing all the ingredients of the spice mix together.
3- Get chicken thighs and use paper towels to remove the moisture from the chicken. Place chicken in a bowl and season with salt. Marinate the chicken with the spice mix. Cover the bowl with Saran Wrap and let it rest in the fridge for at least 2 hours.
4- Strain the cheetos honey. Set aside for later.
5- Mix the oil mix in a pot and heat it up until the brown sugar is completely melted. Set aside for later.
6- Combine dry ingredients and sift them into a bowl (except for the salt that can be poured in without the sift)
7- Mix the wet ingredients together (but leave the egg whites in a separate CLEAN bowl.)
8- combine wet ingredients with dry ingredients and mix.
9- Whip the egg whites until hard peak. Switch to spatula and fold egg whites into wet and dry mix. *DO NOT USE WHISK* This will make the waffle batter.
10- Cook the waffle batter in a waffle maker, 1/2 cup for each waffle.
11- Grab marinated chicken from fridge and make the deep frying batter (lightly mix it together).
12- Mix chicken in flour, then batter then flour once more. Then, carefully place it in the hot oil (be very careful!) to deep fry. Deep fry at 325 Fahrenheit for about 10 - 20 minutes. Cook 2 thighs at a time so you don’t overcrowd the pot. Use a thermometer to check the heat of the oil.
13- Check the chicken’s inner temperature after 10 - 20 minutes using the thermometer. It has to be 165. (If chicken is getting darker but not reaching 165, just finish it in the oven.
14- Brush the oil mix on chicken (make sure it’s hot so that it doesn’t cook the chicken down.
PLATING
15- Brush melted butter onto the waffle and place chicken. Dust with a bit of spice mix and add micro greens if wanted.
Enjoy!

I hope this helped for anyone who wanted to try this! Like this comment to float it to the top for everyone to see!
